You are here: PROMOTE PREDICTION DEFINITIONS AND MODELS TO PRODUCTION

Build and test your models in a sandbox environment and, when itâ€™s production-ready, promote it to your production environment using change sets.

To create an outbound change set:
From Setup, enter change set.
Click New, enter a name and description, then click Save.
Add the prediction by clicking Add next to Change Set Components.
Select Analytics Model, Analytics Model Configuration, or Analytics Model Prediction Definition.
Select one or more deployed prediction definitions or models from the list, and then click Add to Change Set.

Upload the change list to the target production environment. Deploy it as for any other change set.
See Change Sets in Salesforce Help.
